[thinking] I'm thinking about JUnit and its handling of nested classes. If a nested class doesn't have any @Test methods, does that mean it's not valid? But if it includes @Test and is @Nested, then JUnit will register its constructor. However, a non-static nested class requires access to its outer class, which isn’t ideal for testing. I wonder if I could just put the test method in a static nested class, but wait, JUnit doesn't support that for @Nested classes.
